09/04/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Orthodox Christians and Roman Catholics in Southeast Europe and the world celebrated Easter on Sunday (April 8th), as the two religious calendars coincided this year.
Holy Easter liturgies and services were held across the region, and well as in Rome and Jerusalem, featuring prayers for a better future, peace and reconciliation.
In Kosovo, UNMIK chief Joachim Ruecker described Easter as a great holiday that celebrates the ability to forgive.
(Darik, BNR, Tanjug, RTS, HINA, ANA-MPA, KosovaLive - 08/04/07)
